background_story: Sariah, a renowned marine biologist, had always been fascinated by the evolutionary history of vertebrates. Her research focused on the Gnathostomata, a group of jawed vertebrates that include humans, fish, and many other species. She spent years studying the development of jaws in ancient fish, seeking to understand how this crucial innovation allowed Gnathostomata to dominate Earth's oceans. Sariah's groundbreaking discoveries shed new light on the origins of vertebrate diversity, earning her a prestigious award in the field of evolutionary biology. Her work continues to inspire a new generation of scientists, exploring the intricate relationships between species and the secrets hidden within the ancient lineage of the Gnathostomata.
